neither a creature nor subject to change. He is always good, since He is
given by the Father and the Son; neither is He to be numbered amongst
such things as are said to fail. He must be acknowledged as the source
of goodness. The Spirit of God's mouth, the amender of evils, and
Himself good. Lastly, as He is said in Scripture to be good, and is
joined to the Father and the Son in baptism, He cannot possibly be
denied to be good. He is not, however, said to progress, but to be made
perfect in goodness, which distinguishes Him from all
